  "local_port": 58680,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "To clear your Hotmail inbox (now known as Outlook.com), you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Delete Individual Emails**\n   - Open your inbox.\n   - Select the checkbox next to the email(s) you want to delete.\n   - Click the **Delete** (trash bin) icon at the top of the page.\n\n### 2. **Delete Multiple Emails at Once**\n   - Open your inbox.\n   - Click the checkbox at the top of the email list to select all emails on the current page.\n   - If you want to delete more emails, scroll to the bottom of the page and click **Select all conversations in your inbox**.\n   - Click the **Delete** (trash bin) icon.\n\n### 3. **Use Filters to Delete Emails**\n   - Open your inbox.\n   - Use the search bar to filter emails (e.g., by sender, subject, or date).\n   - Select the emails you want to delete and click the **Delete** icon.\n\n### 4. **Archive Emails**\n   - Instead of deleting, you can archive emails to keep them without cluttering your inbox:\n     - Select the emails you want to archive.\n     - Click the **Archive** (folder with a down arrow) icon.\n\n### 5. **Empty the Deleted Items Folder**\n   - Deleted emails are moved to the **Deleted Items** folder. To permanently remove them:\n     - Open the **Deleted Items** folder.\n     - Select the checkbox at the top to choose all emails.\n     - Click the **Delete permanently** option.\n\n### 6. **Use Sweep Rules**\n   - Use the **Sweep** feature to automatically delete or move emails from specific senders:\n     - Select an email from the sender you want to create a rule for.\n     - Click the **Sweep** icon (broom) at the top.\n     - Choose an option (e.g., delete all emails from this sender).\n\n### 7. **Turn on Focused Inbox**\n   - Enable **Focused Inbox** to automatically sort important emails into the \"Focused\" tab and less important ones into the \"Other\" tab:\n     - Click the **Settings** gear icon.\n     - Go to **View all Outlook settings** > **Mail** > **Layout**.\n     - Turn on **Focused Inbox**.\n\nBy following these steps, you can efficiently clear and manage your Hotmail (Outlook.com) inbox.",
